description: SpaceX is targeting Wednesday, July 26 for Falcon Heavy‚Äôs launch of the Hughes JUPITER 3 mission to a geosynchronous transfer orbit from Launch Complex 39A (LC-39A) at Kennedy Space Center in Florida. The 99-minute launch window opens at 11:04 p.m. ET (03:04 UTC on July 27. If needed, a backup launch opportunity is available on Thursday, July 27 with the same window.Both of the side boosters on this mission previously supported USSF-44 and USSF-67. Following stage separation, Falcon Heavy‚Äôs two side boosters will land on SpaceX‚Äôs Landing Zones 1 and 2 (LZ-1 and LZ-2) at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida. A live webcast of this mission will begin about 15 minutes prior to liftoff.

title: 7 Days In The Most Controversial BALCONY Cabin at Sea
tags: cruise|cruise tips|emma cruises|celebrity edge|celebrity infinite veranda|infinite veranda cabin review|celebrity cruises|balcony cabin
description: A balcony cabin, where the balcony is INSIDE the ship? It doesn't sound possible, but it is! I spent 7 days in a Celebrity Edge Infinite Veranda cabin, and here's what I thought. I‚Äôm currently on a cruise and I‚Äôm staying in a balcony cabin that has a feature that I‚Äôve never seen on a cruise ship before. It‚Äôs very different from what you‚Äôd expect when you hear the word balcony and I‚Äôve spent most of this week trying to work out why the cruise line made this decision. I‚Äôve seen and done some things this week that I definitely didn‚Äôt expect when I booked this cruise and picked this cabin.Like quirky cabins? Check out these!My balcony opened onto the PROMENADE DECK: https://youtu.be/Sg9NynxWReMThis cabin had a glass bathroom wall: https://youtu.be/EvhmoI-OJa8The cheapest cabin on a MEGASHIP: https://youtu.be/mKHOhGD9Tp8 Usually when you look at cruise ship balcony cabins they are pretty similar, the designs do change between ships and the layout inside might change but the actual balcony space is pretty standard. It‚Äôs usually a rectangle of some size with two chairs on it, there‚Äôs not much that can be changed with that, maybe the addition of a table if you‚Äôre lucky. The ship that I‚Äôm currently onboard is the Celebrity Edge, built in 2018 she‚Äôs the first in Celebrities edge class of ships. She was game changing for Celebrity in lots of ways and the cabins are no exception. When I booked this cruise I decided to book what is called an Infinite Veranda cabin. There are 918 infinite verandas on this ship and they are 23% bigger than balcony cabins on other Celebrity ships. I usually am an inside cabin kind of girl but I do love a controversial cabin and as I had read lots of very good and very bad reviews about the cabin, I wanted to find out for myself if I would like it. One person described it as a ‚Äòthe best room they‚Äôve ever stayed in‚Äô but another person said that it was so bad that it ‚Äòruined their vacation beyond repair‚Äô. I did have somebody tell me recently though that their cruise was ruined by the library being too cold so I always try to take those reviews with a pinch of salt. The description of the cabin promised to ‚Äòblur the boundary between inside and outside‚Äô and that it definitely did. My cabin was assigned at the time of booking and I was given cabin 7156 towards the front of deck 7. Quite often cruise lines will give you a discount if you don‚Äôt pick your specific cabin location but Celebrity didn‚Äôt have any option for that so I just let my travel agent pick the cabin, I trusted her and in the past I‚Äôve had cabins right at the top of the ship, right at the bottom, at the front, at the back, besides the atrium, under nightclubs, you name it I‚Äôve probably tried it at some point because I am not fussy when it comes to cabin location.The cabin that I was assigned looked good cabin on paper, so I was feeling pretty optimistic and excited. title: We Told The Kids I'm Dying :(
tags: [none]
description: P.O. Box Jenny Appleford7211 Haven Ave, Unit E-407Rancho Cucamonga, CA 91701Kyle‚Äôs Channel:https://www.youtube.com/@kyleapple9702INSTAGRAM: jenny_applefordFACEBOOK: Our Brave Jenny For business inquiries: veganapplefords@gmail.com DIAGNOSIS:March 19th, 2021 Stage IIIA Non Small Cell Lung Cancer (Non-Smoking)February 2022 Stage IV Non Small Cell Lung Cancer (spreading to Brain, and other parts of lung and lymph nodes)Gene Mutation EGFR with Exon 20 InsertionTREATMENTS: Received or currently Receiving2021: 8 Rounds of Chemotherapy (Carboplatin and Paclitaxel) with 30 concurrent radiation treatments to chest and lungFailed Immunotherapy directly after Chemo and Radiation (Durvalumab, 1 round)2022: Chemotherapy10 rounds of Chemotherapy (Carboplatin, Alimta, and Avastin) 6 with Carboplatin, 4 withoutTargeted Brain Radiation (Completed)CURRENT TREATMENT:I am on a clinical trial for my specific gene mutation Our GoFundMe Link:https://gofund.me/5edf81e5The purpose of my channel is to document my cancer journey to look back on, and/or help anyone else going through anything similar. It is also to potentially help loved ones supporting those who are in this fight as well. This is also an easy way to update a lot of people at once. My main goal is to have footage of this journey for my husband and children to look back on. I originally created this channel as a sort of video diary for my family. Thank you so much for following along on this journey. Your love and support help me so much.

title: We Tried BOAT LIFE for 72 Hours (Is it for us?)
tags: boatlife|living on a boat for 72 hours|travel vlog|boat life|sailing la vagabonde|travel scotland|the scottish highlands|van life|boat life tour|living on a boat tour
description: This week we tried #boatlife for the very first time! As newbies we had to learn the ropes (pun intended) we both learned how to drive, navigate, moor and sleep on the boat for 72 hours.We were a little worried how this would go as Aimee can get quite boat sick, but as we were on the Scottish lochs, there wasn't a wave in sight and we honestly had the trip of a lifetime.On this trip we sailed the Caledonian canal on the Great Glen Way. An absolutely stunning part of the Scottish highlands.We left from Inverness and made out way all the way down to Fort Augustus - where we had to use our new found skills on the 6 flight locks! (We had help don't worry!)The full length of the canal is around 60 miles and usually ends in Fort William.It was so exciting to be able to take this HUGE boat out on Loch ness by ourselves - a dream trip and we were lucky enough to get the best weather for it! Seeing Scotland via boat is such a different perspective - We would highly recommend it and it you're nervous about the boat - don't be! If we can do it, so can you.So join us as we give you a full boat tour (this boat actually sleeps 6!) and try to navigate our way around the Scottish highlands on a boat!And a Huge thank you to @visitscotland @caleycruisers7690  and @scottishcanals for inviting us to to the highlands for an incredible trip and putting together a world class itinerary!#Ad #Scotlandiscalling #VisitScotland #CanalMagic ‚≠ê‚≠ê Download our Scotland guide here - https://www.kinging-it.com/mapsüöó Top 10 videos to watch on Kinging-it‚Äôs channel:WATCH HERE! - http://bit.ly/3uHC5sy‚û°Ô∏èüë´ A bit about US- We are Craig and Aimee, from South Wales, UK. title: Marvel Studios' The Marvels | Official Trailer
tags: marvel|comics
description: This fall, The Marvels take flight.Carol Danvers aka Captain Marvel has reclaimed her identity from the tyrannical Kree and taken revenge on the Supreme Intelligence. But unintended consequences see Carol shouldering the burden of a destabilized universe. When her duties send her to an anomalous wormhole linked to a Kree revolutionary, her powers become entangled with that of Jersey City super-fan, Kamala Khan aka Ms. Marvel, and Carol's estranged niece, now S.A.B.E.R. astronaut Captain Monica Rambeau. Together, this unlikely trio must team-up and learn to work in concert to save the universe as The Marvels.Marvel Studios' The Marvels stars Brie Larson, Teyonah Parris, Iman Vellani, Zawe Ashton, Gary Lewis, Park Seo-joon, Zenobia Shroff, Mohan Kapur, Saagar Shaikh, and Samuel L. Jackson.Nia DaCosta directs with Kevin Feige producing. Louis D'Esposito, Victoria Alonso, Mary Livanos, Jonathan Schwartz and Matthew Jenkins serve as executive producers.
